cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.SE

The paper discusses the development of machine learning models (MLP, RBF, RS) for monitoring the condition of oil-filled bushings in transformers. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of majority voting to combine the models, which is a common technique in ensemble learning and could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). The monitoring of transformers is a control systems (cs.SY) application, and the use of rough set theory is a form of data analysis (cs.SE).
